==========================================================
Phase 5-C: Toss confirmPayment behavior — direct API call check
==========================================================

Flow: /api/payments/confirm (POST)
  1. validate payload (paymentKey, orderId, amount, packageId) — catalog SSOT check OK
  2. authenticate (supabase.auth.getUser) — returns 401 if not logged in
  3. await confirmPayment(paymentKey, orderId, parsedAmount) — Toss approve
  4. await addCredits(...) — !!! NO IDEMPOTENCY CHECK !!!
  5. await activateMembershipSubscription(...) — idempotent (single row PK on user_id)
  6. await grantLifetimeReportEntitlement(...) — idempotent (payment_key check)
  7. await grantTasteProductEntitlement(...) — idempotent (payment_key check)
  8. await upsertPaidReadingSnapshot(...) — idempotent (UPSERT)

Risk in production (today as of audit):
  • If /api/payments/confirm is invoked twice with same paymentKey:
    - Step 3 (Toss): returns same approved record (Toss-side idempotent)
    - Step 4 (addCredits): RUNS AGAIN, doubles balance for credit_pack/subscription_bonus packs
    - Step 7 (taste): no-op (already granted)
    - Net effect: user gets DOUBLE COINS for one payment

DONE
